<concept id="concept-2673" xml:lang="en-us" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Quick guide for testers</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author translate="no" type="creator" class="- topic/author ">Yen Nguyen &lt;yen.nguyen@katalon.com&gt;</author><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><keywords class="- topic/keywords "/></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">In this guide, you will take your first steps with <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-platform" class="- topic/ph "/> and  become familiar with some of its basic functions. You will accomplish this by creating your first automated software test in 5  simple steps.</p><section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Requirements</title><p class="- topic/p "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You have created a Katalon account.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You have connected a Git repository for  your project. To learn how to connect the Git repository to your project, refer to this document: <xref href="../../../../Organize/upload-tests-via-git-repo/intro-git-test-project.dita" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You have installed <ph conkeyref="name-variables/ks-ped" class="- topic/ph "/>. To install <ph conkeyref="name-variables/ks-ped" class="- topic/ph "/>, you can refer to this document: <xref href="../../../Katalon_Studio_Installation/Installation_Overview.dita" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p></li></ul></p></section></conbody></concept>